USD coordSys support for MaterialX transformpoint, both fromspace and tospace

Companion to test_2650 — exercises ND_transformpoint_vector3 with both
`fromspace` and `tospace` set to custom coordSys names. Two helpers are
inserted: one on the input side (coordSys -> world) and one on the
output side (world -> coordSys), per the bidirectional handling in
libs/common/materials_utils.cpp.

The MaterialX network feeds an explicit object-space position (driven by
ND_position_vector3 with the standard "object" space) into a
transformpoint that converts from coordSys "src" to coordSys "dst". The
expected output equals the object position translated by the difference
between the two bound Xforms.

PARAMS: {'scene':'test.usda'}
